Package gw.api.json.mapping

Class TransformCache

java.lang.Object
gw.api.json.mapping.TransformCache
public class TransformCache extends Object
This class provides static access to a thread-local Map of values that is automatically created during mapping transforms and then cleared when the transform finishes. The cache persists for the duration of the top-level transformObject or transformObjects call.

    • isActive

      public static boolean isActive()
      Indicates whether the TransformCache is active. This method will return true if a mapping transform is currently being evaluated, and false otherwise.
      Returns:
      true if the TransformCache is active, false otherwise

    • containsKey

      public static boolean containsKey(Object key)
      Indicates whether the given key is present in the TransformCache. This method will throw an exception if the TransformCache is not active.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to check
      Returns:
      true if the key is present in the TransformCache, false otherwise

    • containsKeyIfActive

      public static boolean containsKeyIfActive(Object key)
      Indicates whether the given key is present in the TransformCache. This method will return false if the TransformCache is not active.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to check
      Returns:
      true if the key is present in the TransformCache, false otherwise or if the TransformCache is not active

    • getIfActive

      Returns:
      the value of the key in the TransformCache, or null if the key is not present or if the cache is not active

    • put

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the previous value associated with the key, or null if the key was not present or if the cache is not active

    • computeIfAbsent

      public static <V> V computeIfAbsent(Object key, Function<? super Object,? extends V> mappingFunction)
      If the given key is present in the TransformCache, returns its current value. Otherwise, evaluates the provided mappingFunction, adds the resulting value to the cache using the given key, and returns the value. This method will throw an exception if the TransformCache is not active.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to retrieve or add
      mappingFunction - a Function that takes the provided key as its only argument and returns the value that should be added to the map
      Returns:
      the current value of the given key, if present, or the result of evaluating the mappingFunction

    • computeIfAbsentIfActive

      public static <V> V computeIfAbsentIfActive(Object key, Function<? super Object,? extends V> mappingFunction)
      If the given key is present in the TransformCache, returns its current value. Otherwise, evaluates the provided mappingFunction, adds the resulting value to the cache using the given key, and returns the value. This method will always evaluate the mappingFunction and return its value if the cache is not active.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to retrieve or add
      mappingFunction - a Function that takes the provided key as its only argument and returns the value that should be added to the map
      Returns:
      the current value of the given key, if present and the cache is active, or the result of evaluating the mappingFunction
